    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>Sketch the angle <m>\theta = \frac{\pi}{ {{denom}} }</m> on the unit circle. 
            Then give the values of <m>\cos\left( \frac{\pi}{ {{denom}} } \right)</m> 
            and <m>\sin\left( \frac{\pi}{ {{denom}} } \right)</m>.</p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p><m>{\large Answer}</m></p>
           <p>
                <image
                    source = "../assets/PR1/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show1.png"
                    description = "The given first-quadrant angle"
                />
            </p>
            <p>
            The cosine of the given angle is <m>{{cosQ1}}</m>. 
            The sine of the given angle is <m>{{sinQ1}}</m>.
            </p>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>
